properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - ST PETERS Sydney Park Road at Euston Rd and Huntley St
properties.otherAdvice:
Permanent traffic changes at the intersection of Sydney Park Rd, Euston Rd and Huntley St from 9pm Fri 17th Apr:
- Euston Rd will be increased to three lanes in both northbound and southbound directions between Campbell Rd and Sydney Park Rd.
- The Euston Rd and Sydney Park Rd intersection will be opened to its permanent arrangement at the intersection. This will include the new ‘No Right Turn’ restriction for Euston Rd southbound traffic.
- The intersection of Euston Rd, Sydney Park Rd and Huntley St will be opened to its permanent arrangement.
- Euston Rd will be provided as two right turn lanes and one left turn lane in a temporary arrangement at the Campbell Rd intersection.
- Euston Rd southbound straight through lanes to the new M5 Tunnel will be closed at the Campbell Rd intersection. 

In addition - from 9pm Fri 17 Apr there will be:
- A full road closure will be in place on Euston Rd between Maddox St and Campbell Rd. Local business access will be provided on Euston Rd under the direction of traffic control. 
- Stop/slow traffic management will also be in place along Sydney Park Rd between Mitchell Rd and Euston Rd, Alexandria.

properties.headline: COVID-19 Border Controls - NSW-SOUTH AUSTRALIA Border crossings
properties.otherAdvice:

properties.headline: COVID-19 Border Controls - NSW-QUEENSLAND Border crossings
properties.otherAdvice:
The Queensland state government has imposed restrictions on cross-border movements as a result of the coronavirus pandemic.

Restrictions in effect include border road closures and police checks on vehicles on major highways.

Exemptions include freight, emergency vehicles and emergency workers, people travelling to and from work, court orders including family court, compassionate grounds and medical treatment.

properties.headline: COVID-19 Border Controls - NSW-QUEENSLAND M1 Pacific Motorway approaching Queensland border
properties.otherAdvice:
The Queensland state government has imposed restrictions on cross-border movements as a result of the coronavirus pandemic.

  • Queensland, Heavy & Exempt vehicles should remain on the motorway
  • All other vehicles must exit onto the Gold Coast Hwy where there will be a police checkpoint

Exemptions include freight, emergency vehicles and emergency workers, people travelling to and from work, court orders including family court, compassionate grounds and medical treatment.

Visit qld.gov.au for more details.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS New clearway times - RYDE TO EPPING Blaxland Road between Devlin Street, Ryde AND Epping Road
properties.otherAdvice:
From Monday 6 April, new clearway times will come into effect in both directions on Blaxland Rd between Devlin St, Ryde and Epping Rd, Epping.

Currently, southbound clearways are in operation during the morning peak, while northbound clearways are in operation during the afternoon/evening peak.

The new arrangements will see clearways in force in both directions from 6am-10am and 3pm-7pm.

Vehicles parked in clearways during their hours of operation are at risk of being towed and fines applied.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS WestConnex - ROZELLE Terry Street at Victoria Rd
properties.otherAdvice:
From 10pm Thursday April 2:

  • There will be no access to Victoria Rd from Terry St – Terry St will be one-way northbound 
  • Southbound traffic wishing to access Victoria Rd, please use Wellington St 
  • Motorists will still be able to enter Terry St from Victoria Rd, as per current arrangements          
  • There will be no access to Crystal St from Terry St 
  • To access Crystal St, motorists are advised to use Victoria Rd westbound and turn around via Park Ave, Formosa St, Henley Marine Dr and Victoria Rd eastbound.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - WOODBURN Pacific Highway
properties.publicTransport: Bus services will continue with no changes to existing bus stop locations.
properties.otherAdvice:
Local traffic will be moved onto the new overpass bridge and northbound off-ramp of the Woodburn interchange, weather permitting.
- As part of this change, the existing intersection of the Pacific Hwy and Tuckombil Rd near The Gap Rd will permanently close.  
- Access to and from the highway will be maintained for local traffic via the intersection of Trustums Hill Rd and the Pacific Hwy, and the new overpass bridge at the Woodburn interchange.  
- This will be a detour of about six kilometres for motorists travelling south.  
- Motorists travelling north on the Pacific Hwy will be able to exit via the new northbound off-ramp. These changes will affect motorists wanting to access Tuckombil Rd, The Gap Rd, Bundjalung National Park, Tuckombil Rd, The Gap Rd, Sharpe Rd, Brickella Rd and the Bundjalung National Park and Black Rocks Campground.

Motorists are advised to drive to the conditions, and follow the directions of signs and traffic control.

properties.headline: COVID-19 - STAY AT HOME - Avoid non-essential travel
properties.otherAdvice:
To help stop the spread of Covid-19, NSW residents are urged to stay at home over the Easter long weekend and the April school holidays.

Under public health orders in force in NSW, you are advised to cancel travel plans and stay at home unless you are going to work or school, shopping for essentials, obtaining medical care or exercising.
